### Key Findings

- **Root cause confirmed**: `RAILWAY_TOKEN` is invalid/expired — the CI pre-flight `{me{id}}` GraphQL call returns `Not Authorized`. Same issue as #740 and #741.
- **Immediate fix**: Create a new token at https://railway.com/account/tokens, then `gh secret set RAILWAY_TOKEN --repo alexsiri7/reli`, then rerun job `25007185051`.
- **Token type**: Railway explicitly recommends **workspace-scoped tokens** (not account tokens) for "team CI/CD, shared automation" — the current setup uses an account token per DEPLOYMENT_SECRETS.md. Switching to workspace scope is safer and may reduce future rotation issues.
- **Dashboard API tokens are long-lived** (no documented expiry), so the recurring failures (#740, #741, #742) are likely due to the token being revoked or deleted in the Railway dashboard, not an inherent expiry.

### Gaps

- Why tokens keep expiring within days of rotation is not explained by Railway's public docs — requires inspection of the Railway dashboard to see if tokens are showing as "revoked."

